## Decisions Made
- Keep decision commits on existing durable path: Peer review (3/3 consensus) identified durability regression — decisions in gitignored tmp could be lost on session crash
- Use tmp/ (project root) instead of .knowledge/tmp/ for vault-refs: Avoids conflict with .knowledge/ direct read prohibition in AGENTS.md
- vault-refs are best-effort with unconditional cleanup: Loss on note failure is acceptable for supplementary signal
- Markdown-only format (no JSON appendix): Consistent with existing 5-section approach, avoids dual-format complexity
- Memento remains optional evidence: Pipeline works without vault-refs
- No session scoping for tmp files: Single session is standard, worktree isolation handles concurrency
- followed signals excluded from _vault_feedback: YAGNI — can be added later without breaking changes
- Part C artifact cleanup as separate workflow step: Ensures cleanup runs even when vault.db is unchanged

## Problems Encountered
- Peer review identified 6 design issues requiring resolution before implementation: Resolved through structured discussion — each issue reviewed with user, decisions documented in plan
- Initial plan had record-decision moving to tmp (breaking durability): Resolved by keeping hybrid approach — decisions commit, memento references by slug/SHA
- knowledge-gate rule 6 initially inserted inside Question Protocol section: Fixed by correcting insertion point

## Constraints Identified
- .knowledge/ directory must not be read directly by agents: All vault access through knowledge-gate CLI, vault-refs stored in tmp/ instead
- Backward compatibility required for 5-section mementos: collect-evidence defaults vault_refs and decision_refs to empty arrays for legacy format

